ed range. We\ntake advantage of such a technology by carrying out surface enhanced Raman\nspectroscopy (SERS) on Brilliant Cresyl Blue molecules deposited onto plasmonic\nSCs. We achieve a broadband SERS enhancement factor up to $10^{4}$, thereby\nproviding a proof-of-concept application for chemical diagnostics.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 9 Apr 2018 08:42:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-04-19"}
