laced toward summer in the northern\nhemisphere. Objects of this size contribute negligibly to the exogenous species\nand dust in the stratosphere of Jupiter when compared with the continuous flux\nfrom interplanetary dust punctuated by giant impacts. Flashes of a high enough\ncould produce an observable debris field on the planet. We estimate that a\ncontinuous search for these impacts might find these events once every 0.4 to\n2.6 years.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 9 Apr 2018 14:13:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-09-19"}
